<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[270,1103,878,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,410,878,899]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body oval­convex. Integument black with yellow spots on pronotum and elytra (
<figureCitation box="[461,543,906,927]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[293,336,1089,1108]" captionTargetBox="[366,1006,234,1069]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[366,1006,234,1069]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 15–18. 15) Hinda buqueti; 16) Hinda decas; 17) Hinda designata; 18) Hinda modesta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900197/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Pronotum black at base, with two projections towards apex forming letter ‘‘M’’. Scutellum black. Each elytron with five large spots: the first oval and basal; the second, smallest, on humeral callus; the third, below first, close to suture, approximately same size as first, quadrangular, with oblique base and truncate apex; the fourth linked to external elytral border, with small central constriction and with rounded internal borders; fifth spot apical, oval, linked to external border. Length 
<quantity box="[806,962,1072,1093]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.08" metricValueMin="3.92" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="4.08" valueMin="3.92">3.92–4.08 mm</quantity>
. Width 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.29" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.08" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="3.29" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="3.08">3.08– 3.50 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[270,1103,878,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,359,1127,1148]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Male.</emphasis>
Median lobe symmetrical, with rounded apex, shorter than parameres. Parameres wide at base and constricted at apical apical where they narrow and turn outward to end in rounded point (
<figureCitation box="[696,779,1183,1204]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[291,334,1174,1193]" captionTargetBox="[375,995,237,1153]" captionTargetId="figure-12@7.[374,996,234,1154]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 26–27. Hinda decas. 26) tegmen; 27) sipho." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900207/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Sipho curved, with truncate apex and membranous projections (
<figureCitation box="[652,733,1211,1232]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[291,334,1174,1193]" captionTargetBox="[375,995,237,1153]" captionTargetId="figure-12@7.[374,996,234,1154]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 26–27. Hinda decas. 26) tegmen; 27) sipho." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900207/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[270,1103,878,1620]" box="[296,503,1238,1259]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,384,1238,1259]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[270,1103,878,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,405,1266,1287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weise Gordon" authorityYear="1971" box="[414,548,1266,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decas">
<emphasis box="[414,548,1266,1287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Hinda decas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant. Crotch" authorityYear="1874" box="[671,808,1266,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="designata">
<emphasis box="[671,808,1266,1287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">H. designata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in color and in position of the spots, and in the symmetrical lobes of the male genitalia. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weise Gordon" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decas">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">H. decas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have the central spot of the elytral disc, and other aspects of the male genitalia are different. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weise Gordon" authorityYear="1971" box="[640,734,1350,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decas">
<emphasis box="[640,734,1350,1371]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">H. decas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the parameres are narrow near the apex, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant. Crotch" authorityYear="1874" box="[437,575,1377,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="designata">
<emphasis box="[437,575,1377,1398]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">H. designata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are wide and concave at the apex. It (and that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant. Crotch" authorityYear="1874" box="[349,485,1405,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="designata">
<emphasis box="[349,485,1405,1426]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">H. designata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[679,786,1405,1426]" name="Colombia" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="74" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[270,1103,878,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,469,1432,1453]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Type Material.</emphasis>
One specimen of 
<emphasis box="[681,784,1433,1454]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weise Gordon" authorityYear="1971" box="[681,780,1433,1454]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decas">H. decas</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
indicated by Weise as from Thieme, 
<collectingCountry box="[364,470,1460,1481]" name="Colombia" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, Manizales (Patino), with a hand­written label 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weise Gordon" authorityYear="1971" box="[970,1102,1461,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decas">
<emphasis box="[970,1102,1461,1482]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Hinda decas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m., possesses two additional labels: one printed ‘‘Zool. Mus. Berlin’’ and the other with: ‘‘ 
<typeStatus box="[404,517,1516,1537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Lectotype</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Weise Gordon 1971" authorityName="Weise Gordon" authorityYear="1971" box="[529,888,1516,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decas">
<emphasis box="[529,663,1516,1537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Hinda decas</emphasis>
Weise Gordon 1971
</taxonomicName>
,’’ the designation of which was unpublished. This material is deposited in the ZMHU.
</paragraph>
